We're coming to a close on the [Series 3 Kickstarter for our commercial edition of Pocket-Tactics](https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/illgottengames/pocket-tactics-series-3-new-dominion/description) (the 3d print-and-play strategy board game that you might have seen kicking around over the last 10 years), and we wanted to share a couple of free mercenary units that can be brought in to add some extra flavor to your custom force builds. This is my entry for the next [28mag challenge](https://28-mag.com/2021/01/12/the-28magchallenge-for-2021/).

Beltanya Zukhal is a legal clerc of the Administratum whose task is to record anything and everything, from dead fluotubes to Astra Militarum empty Autocannon cases and daily casualty on the battlefield. She even records the number of downloads of her STL template.
As part of her missions, she frequently goes on field trips to accompany Regimental HQ staff (where she carries a sidearm for self defence).

It is on one of such missions that she met with Inquisitor Johevian of the Ordo Aegis. Now she works for him undercover and has even been sighted with him as part of his retinue.

As always, "Watch" if you want to be informed of any updates.

I remixed this pieces from my [scap box](https://www.thingiverse.com/mangforge/collections/scrap-box):
 + [Laspistol](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:3559689)
 + [Gothic dataslate](https://www.thingiverse.com/thing:4800103)

Come support these models over on [Patreon](https://www.patreon.com/WGraves)
**Buy my time, Not my models.**

Near future combat (or not) drones at 1/100 (15mm). Designed to print on a filament printer so you can bend the fans to suit, I don't have a resin printer but I don't think resin will bend like that, I may be wrong. These are shown in the photograph next to a rebelminis 15mm operator in red, and a plastic soldier company 15mm WW2 German for scale.

These are freakishly small to trim and assemble. The little dot attached to the back of the guns is there to fold over and act as a standoff from the drone body.

I would suggest just printing the "drones sampler" file as it makes 1 of each size and type of drone, all the bases, and 3 sets of weapons.
